KNOWN LIMITATION (documented in design § Future work, EDGE-008)
---------------------------------------------------------------
Curl with LinkedInBot UA returns the static index.html with
<title>Newsletter archive</title> only. SPA-injected og:title is not
visible to scrapers that don't execute JS. This is pre-existing SPA
behavior, not a regression. Fix is SSR or bot-UA HTML stub — out of
scope for VER-68. First-time LinkedIn/X share previews may show
"Newsletter archive"; subsequent re-scrapes after enabling SSR will
update.

Sample of what scrapers see:
  $ curl -sL -A 'LinkedInBot/1.0' \
      https://email-centered-wondering-classics.trycloudflare.com/archive/<runId>
  HTTP 200, 1076 bytes
  <title>Newsletter archive</title>
  (no og:title meta in static HTML)
